# .dockerignore — build-context trim list.
#
# docker build does NOT read .gitignore, so this file is the only
# lever that keeps junk (dev-cache/, .claude/, scratch files) out
# of the image build context. Without it, the full working tree
# is shipped to the daemon on every build, which once dev-cache/
# is populated means tens of GB of pointless bytes per build.
#
# This mirrors the spirit of .gitignore — if git shouldn't track it,
# docker shouldn't build on top of it either. Runtime state that
# lives in bind-mounted volumes (dev-cache/, host caches rebound
# via docker-compose.warm.yml) is layered in at container-start
# time, never baked into image layers, so excluding it here is
# always correct.

# Git + local tooling
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.dockerignore
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Dev cache — the whole point is to keep this OUT of build context.
# Bind-mounted at runtime via docker-compose.dev.yml (repo-local) or
# docker-compose.warm.yml (host-direct). Never baked into image layers.
dev-cache/

# Native dev runtime staging (same reasoning — bind-mounted at runtime)
scripts/splash/status/.native-run/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/

# Logs & scratch
*.log
*.tmp
.scratch*

# Secrets (defense in depth — none exist today, but guard future)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
secrets.json
credentials.json

# Large model artifacts — images pull these at runtime via the
# hf_hub client / ollama, never COPY them during build.
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.ckpt
*.pth
*.pt
*.onnx
*.bin
.cache/
huggingface/

# Note: `models/` is NOT excluded here even though .gitignore lists it,
# because docker/**/models/ is whitelisted in .gitignore and some
# Dockerfiles may legitimately want to COPY small marker files from
# those paths. If you add a top-level models/ dir with big weights,
# add `models/` + `!docker/**/models/` here too.

# HANDOFF notes live at repo root but aren't image material
HANDOFF.md
